    "summary": "The ABI Sea Surface Temperature (SST) is calculated using a 4-band (8.44, 10.33, 11.19, and 12.27 um) non-linear SST (NLSST) regression equation with coefficients calculated using match-ups with in situ SSTs from drifting and tropical moored buoys. Hence on average, ABI SST is close to in situ (bulk) SST, but its spatial and temporal variations are representative of skin SST (to which ABI BTs are sensitive).
